<P>
   BUDGET-U.S. (Washington) _ The House and Senate passed the
Republican budget plan Thursday night, driving toward a big tax cut
and a showdown later this year with the Clinton administration over
priorities in an era of fiscal plenty. The GOP budget calls for a
tax cut of nearly $800 billion over the next 10 years, an increase
in Pentagon spending and more money for education. By Richard W.
Stevenson. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   NURSING-HOMES (Washington) _ President Clinton signs legislation
that prohibits nursing homes from evicting Medicaid patients, as
some have done (so they can take other patients who pay more than
Medicaid). By Robert Pear. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-JUROR-INTERVIEW (Washington) _ The grand jury forewoman
in the Monica Lewinsky scandal said in an interview that she would
have indicted President Clinton for perjury if she had been asked
to. By Frank Bruni.
</P>
