<SLUG> BC-GAME-EATING-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GAME MEAT CONTRIBUTES TO A HEALTHFUL DIET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By G.J. SAGI  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TUCSON, Ariz. _ While eating healthful foods and losing weight
may seem nearly impossible-to-keep resolutions, the answer for many
people is easier than you might think.
</P>
<P>
   Most game meats have fewer calories and contain less fat than
conventional meats sold at the supermarket. While 100 grams of
uncooked lean hamburger contains 272 calories and 18 grams of fat,
the same amount of deer meat has only 120 calories and 2 grams of
fat. A person can consume 56 percent fewer calories by simply
substituting ground venison for hamburger.
</P>
<P>
   Elk has only 111 calories per 100 grams of meat, and 1 gram of
fat. Antelope has 114 calories with 2 grams of fat; even a meat
considered ``greasy,'' like bear, has only 161 calories and 8 grams
of fat.
</P>
<P>
   As an added bonus, game meat does not contain any of the
steroids or antibiotics often found in retail meats.
</P>
<P>
   In other words, game meat is healthier.
</P>
<P>
   And hunting is a physically demanding activity.
</P>
<P>
   Properly prepared venison, antelope and most wild game have a
flavor that rivals meat found in the grocery store. Regardless of
the recipe, elk or caribou simply tastes better than the finest cut
of beef, pork or chicken.
</P>
<P>
   Then there's the fact that sportsmen contribute toward wildlife
conservation through a variety of federal excise taxes, hunting
permits, license fees and voluntary contributions. Through their
efforts, the Rocky Mountain elk, pronghorn antelope and many other
species have been brought back from the brink of extinction.
</P>
<P>
   There are those who oppose hunting, the consumption of meat and,
in fact, any use of animals. Their beliefs have developed after
years of humans being divorced from the land and its often harsh
reality, thanks to our ongoing urban migration. They tout
alternatives to meat consumption that, they say, can also reduce
calorie and fat intake.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, they also dispute _ for purely political reasons
_ the healthful alternative of substituting or adding game meat to
your diet. Some people routinely accept the notion that eating more
healthful foods means eliminating large amounts of meat from the
diet, even though a diet at least partially composed of wild game
meat can be easily adapted to a person's preferred recipes while
providing protein with lower fat and calorie content.
</P>
<P>
   While eating more healthily may seem an insurmountable
challenge, the real challenge is to hold onto those things that are
good while filtering out the din created by media that feed on
politically motivated controversy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
