<SLUG> BC-FILM-REVIEW-20-DATES-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`20 DATES' IS ALL ABOUT EGO 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By WESLEY MORRIS  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``20 Dates'' is about a moron _ oxy and otherwise. A neurotic
jerk of a struggling actor looking for true love in Hollywood. It's
a documentary meant to be the personal journey soul-searching kind,
akin to Ross McEwee's ``Sherman's March.''
</P>
<P>
   Only Myles Berkowitz doesn't appear to have a soul, just an ego
that fails to grasp why women don't love him.
</P>
<P>
   In a fit of frustration with his single, thirtysomething
lifestyle, Berkowitz embarks on a mission to find the truth about
himself by going out on 20 dates with 20 different women. Whether
filmmaking is cheaper than just going to see an actual therapist is
up in the air, but what therapist would allow a guy as irritating
as Berkowitz to whine-and-dine her?
</P>
<P>
   It helps to consider ``20 Dates'' as Woody Allen's ``Private
Parts.''
</P>
<P>
   Berkowitz amply deprecates himself so as to deflect the
possibility that you might find him annoying. He's basically saying
``I already know I'm irritating.'' So why stoop to the level of
desperate self-sploitation that Berkowitz does? What part of
``You're a jerk, buddy'' doesn't he understand?
</P>
<P>
   Therein lies the crumb of this movie's charm: He just wants to
be loved. Is that so wrong? Well, when you're showing up to blind
dates with a cameraman and a sound guy, something's wrong. Many of
the women filmed don't seem to take to Berkowitz's self-promoting
in the first place, then a few notice the camera lens poking out
from behind palm fronds in a restaurant.
</P>
<P>
   Berkowitz includes footage of him being hit by angry women, of
his ex-wife telling him why their marriage broke up. But things get
downright bizarre as Berkowitz actually falls for Elizabeth, one of
the middle dates.
</P>
<P>
   She reciprocates as he's forced to continue to fill the date
quota by the film's unseen but heard Russian producer named Ilie,
who insists the director film dates with only ``hot'' women.
</P>
<P>
   Elizabeth actually grows distraught as the Myles Berkowitz show
goes on. She should be able to see that at times Berkowitz doesn't
really want a girlfriend, he wants a star on the Hollywood Walk of
Fame.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-26-99 1436EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
