<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ NATO unleashes its first daytime
missile attack against Yugoslavia as President Clinton and
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright make radio appeals to the
Yugoslav people to support efforts to stop ethnic aggression in the
Serbian province of Kosovo. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-LIMITS (Washington) _ As NATO warplanes attack
Yugoslavia, U.S. strategists say past U.S. military operations show
that aerial assaults alone won't compel an adversary to capitulate.
By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   JUDGE-INDICT (Undated) _ At least 55 criminal defendants may
have to be re-indicted in the Texas counties of Burleson and
Washington because of Judge Harold Towslee's misunderstanding about
the term of service for grand juries he empaneled. Questions also
are being raised about the status of people convicted in the court
over the past 10 years. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKC-NCAA (St. Petersburg, Fla.) _ Advance on Final Four focusing
