<P>
   WASHINGTON _ President Clinton sent Americans to their almanacs
for a crash course on the Balkans this week, but the lesson has
failed to convince a skeptical public that Kosovo is worth dying
for. After three days of U.S. and NATO air strikes against Serbian
forces, polls consistently show that Americans are confused about
the roots of the conflict, pessimistic about the chance of success
and deeply concerned about the possible loss of American lives. By
RON HUTCHESON. Story will move in ``w'' Washington category. &QL; 
