<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ So let's assume that the president of the United
States has led the world's lone remaining superpower into the
quicksand of a European civil war because he believes it's the
right thing to do. The question then becomes: What in the world
makes him think that this terrible misuse of American firepower is
right, either as a matter of principle or as a matter of sensible
foreign policy? By BILL THOMPSON. Story has moved in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LABBE-COLUMN &QL;
