</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-STRIKES _ WASHINGTON _ U.S.-led NATO air strikes against
Serb military forces in Yugoslavia continue for a third day.
Lead-all. Developing. (Deans-Holmes, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-AVIANO _ AVIANO AIR FORCE BASE, Italy _ As NATO bombers
and fighter jets take off and land here en route to and returning
from military targets in Yugoslavia, the lives of the people living
around this base have been disrupted. Developing. (Holmes, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MILITARY _ WASHINGTON _ After three days of bombing,
what's the Pentagon's assessment? Where does the campaign go from
here? What hardware will be brought to bear next at an enemy that
doesn't appear to be shooting back? Will the Allies get more
involved? Developing. (Shepard, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEES _ SKOPJE, Macedonia _ An update on the refugee
situation in this already-troubled neighboring country that is
catching a lot of the spillover from the problems in Kosovo.
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-BASEBALL _ MIAMI _ Baseball diplomacy. Music diplomacy.
There's all kinds of diplomacy going on between Cuba and the United
States. Ironically, it comes at the same time other nations
generally soft onCuba, such as Canada and the European Union, are
rethinking their relationship with Cuba due to a recent crackdown
on dissidents. On Sunday (3/28), the Baltimore Orioles will become
the first Major League Baseball team to play in Cuba in more than
40 years. (Emling, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED in the (i) International and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-BUTTERFLIES _ EL ROSARIO, Mexico _ It's a phenomenon of
nature that's older than modern humans. Yet within our lifetime, we
may destroy it. The miraculous journey of the Monarch butterflies
from Canada, through the United States and into Mexico and back is
one of the world's greatest natural events. (Ferriss, Cox News
Service).
