<SLUG> BC-BENIGNI-SPEECH-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NOW THAT'S ITALIAN!
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies BENIGNI-OSCAR) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   So just what did Roberto Benigni say when he accepted those
Oscars? Here's our translation:
</P>
<P>
   BEST FOREIGN FILM (presented by Sophia Loren):
</P>
<P>
   Thank you! Oh, grazie! Grazie! Thank you, Sophia! I
(unintelligible) the Oscar, but I want you! I want to be rocketed
by the waves of your beauty! Come here! Thank you! Thank you! This
is a moment of joy! And I want to kiss everybody because you are
the measure of the joy! And he who kisses the joy as it flies,
lives an eternity sunrise, said the poet! (Note: That's what we
heard. The captioning read `` ... lives entirely in our eyes.'')
And this is wonderful to be here! Wonderful! I feel like now, ready
to ... to ... to dive in this ocean of generosity! This is too
much! Your generosity _ is an uh, how do you say, the rain ... the
... the ... the hailstorm! It's a hailstorm of ... of ... of
kindness, of gratitude for you. And really, I'd like to thank
everybody did the movie, because without them I couldn't fly with
this movie! Everybody who did, the producer, the screenwriter,
(unintelligible) ... Harvey Weinstein of Miramax Films, thank you
very much for what you did! And also I would like to thank my
parents in (unintelligible), the little village in Italy. They gave
me the biggest gift of all _ poverty, and I want to thank them for
the rest of my life! Really, but thank you Mama and Papa! And thank
you for your love! Because the reason I am here is because people
loved the movie! It's always a question of love! I would like to
dedicate this prize to those who are not here! They gave their life
in order we can say, `Life is beautiful!' And I would like to say,
a kiss to Giorgio Cantarini, Giorgio the little boy (who played
Benigni's son in the movie), and because we are talking the love,
(speaks Italian) ... and love is a divinity. Sometimes, if you are
afraid, like all the divinities, it can appear. That's why I want
to dedicate this prize to Nicoletta Braschi (Benigni's wife and
co-star)!''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   BEST ACTOR
</P>
<P>
   ``Thank you! This is a terrible mistake, because I used up all
my English! I don't know ... (stammers) ... I'm not able to express
all my gratitude because my body is in tumult! Because it's a
colossal moment of joy! So I-I-I (fumbles for words) cannot
express! I would like to be Jupiter and kidnap everybody and lie
down in the firmament making love to everybody! Because I don't
know how to express _ It's a question of love! This is a mountain
of snow so delicate, and the suavity and kindness, and it's
something I cannot forget from the bottom of my heart! Thank you
for the Academy Awards, for who really loved the movie, thank you
to all _ in Italy, for the Italian cinema, grazie Italia!''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
