<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Saturday, March 27, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   MANN-BIDS (Los Angeles) _ It's nothing like the massive lines
expected for ``Star Wars Episode I: Phantom Menace,'' but the
troubled Mann Theatres chain has drawn several bids since putting
itself up for sale two months ago. By Dave McNary. (Will move in
the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   PINKERTON-ACQUIRE (Los Angeles) _ Sweden's Securitas AB
completed its tender offer for shares of Pinkerton's Inc., the
companies announced Friday, all but ending the independent life of
one of the West's most storied businesses. The New York Stock
Exchange suspended trade on Pinkerton's shares, since Securitas'
tender offer netted 99.3 percent of the shares outstanding. By
Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
