<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ NATO unleashes its third night of air
raids on Yugoslavia. Earlier, President Clinton and Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright made radio appeals to the Yugoslav people
to support efforts to stop ethnic aggression in the Serbian
province of Kosovo. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-LIMITS (Washington) _ As NATO warplanes attack
Yugoslavia, U.S. strategists say past U.S. military operations show
that aerial assaults alone won't compel an adversary to capitulate.
By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ATHEIST-CASE (Undated) _ A second ex-convict who is a possible
figure in the 1995 disappearance of atheist Madalyn Murray O'Hair
is ordered held in a Michigan jail on federal firearms charges.
Meanwhile, a Texan who once worked for O'Hair remained in jail on
the same federal charges. By JOHN MacCORMACK. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
