<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Top players in BellSouth
 &HT;    By Glenn Sheeley
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PONTE VEDRA BEACH, Fla. _ Positioned as the preliminary to the
Masters for only the second time in its history, next week's
BellSouth Classic at the TPC at Sugarloaf clearly has upgraded its
field.
</P>
<P>
   Although without defending champion Tiger Woods, the tournament
will feature two of the world's top three players _ No. 2 David
Duval and No. 3 Davis Love III of Sea Island _ and an international
contingent headed by No. 8 Colin Montgomerie of Scotland.
</P>
<P>
   Also in the 144-player field are Fred Couples (12), Phil
Mickelson (13), Jumbo Ozaki (14), Lee Janzen (21) and John Huston
(24) and Sugarloaf architect Greg Norman (31). Tournament winners
from 1999 include Duval (Mercedes Championship, Bob Hope Chrysler
Classic) and Sweden's Gabriel Hjertstedt (Tucson).
</P>
<P>
   Other prominent international players in the field include
former Masters champions Nick Faldo of England, Jose Maria Olazabal
of Spain and Ian Woosnam of Wales; and Spain's Miguel Angel
Jimenez.
</P>
<P>
   Among the other PGA Tour players in the field are 1995 champion
Mark Calcavecchia, Brad Faxon, Billy Mayfair, Bob Tway, Atlanta's
Stewart Cink and Billy Andrade, Scott Verplank and 1996 champion
Paul Stankowski. Late additions to the field Friday were John Cook,
Glen Day, Jay Haas, Neal Lancaster and Stuart Appleby.
</P>
