<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, MARCH 27
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CHINA-NUKE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Mar. 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Mar. 23,
about Wen Ho Lee, a scientist who has been dismissed from Los
Alamos National Laboratory for security breaches, misspelled the
surname of the senior Democrat on the House committee investigating
unauthorized transfers of military technology to China. He is
Representative Norm Dicks of Washington, not Norm Dix.
</P>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-REPORTERS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Mar. 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Mar. 25,
about Serbia's expulsion of some foreign reporters misstated the
nationality of Peter Finn, a correspondent for The Washington Post
who was detained by the police and then expelled. While he is
expected to have United States citizenship by next week, he is an
Irish citizen, not an American.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GEEK-NOTES-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Mar. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Mar.
24, misstated the given name of the chief executive of Food.com and
described his history at the company incorrectly. He is Rich Frank,
not Robert. He joined the company in 1998, when it was called
Cybermeals.com; he was not a founder of it.
</P>
